	Let's make user interfaces better by writing better user
	interfaces, not by thinking about transferring huge zones between
	servers or about doing network broadcasts.

This is certainly a motherhood statement with which I can hardly
disagree; what I'm still looking for, though, is how to get the
information that is needed for a better user interface without
transferring zones or doing broadcasts. I'm not trying to be
argumentative; I'm trying to gain new knowledge about how the domain
system can be made to work for users. 

Cheers,
chris

